Microsoft System Center Configuration Manager

1. Minimises manual tasks
2. Maximize software investments
3. Compliance management
4. Asset management


SCCM deployment:
1. Can be deployed in single server.
2. Can be deployed in more than 1 server.
3. Can be deployed in hierarchy.

CAS: Central administrative site 
     Child administrative site
     Standalone administrative site

  CAS : 
    1. Used for large scale deployments
    2. Manages other sites
    3. Devices are managed seperatly
    4. I CAS can manage 1 million sites.

  Standalone primary site:
    1. Small scale deployments
    2. Manages devices directly

Roles available
  Ex: 1. Distribution point

